newsletters.title: ASHES OF ARRIVAL
newsletters.content:
There was a time before the tribes.

Not peace. No—peace is a word the wasteland forgot. But there was a stillness. The kind that follows catastrophe. A long, bitter silence, where the world dared not breathe too loudly for fear of waking something older than ruin.

Now? That stillness is shattered. The tribes are moving. And worse—they’re organising.

The first chiefs have stepped out from smoke and shadow. Not just leaders. Symbols. Threats. Promises.

And the ground trembles with every new name spoken.

👑 THE CHIEFS DESCEND
They did not all come at once. No, the wasteland loves theatre—and this was a grand entrance.

From the ashlands, the first banner fluttered. Finland, draped in scorched cloth, stepped forward beneath the cracked standard of The Scorched Earth. No herald. No song. Just a stare, and then scouts—three of them—vanishing into the wild in different directions. Finland’s rule began with a whisper, and whispers are what carry in the dark.

Deep in the southern ruins, they came not one at a time, but in numbers.

Brian McClair, thought to be a relic, now breathes with new life under Glindex's command. Four chiefs answered the call in quick succession:

Synth, silent as circuitry

Mara Solis, whose eyes shimmer like broken glass

Mina Shae, a tactician with teeth

Fizzell, the one with the ledger—rumoured to keep the death toll balanced in ink

What they’ve done since arriving, no one knows. But strange lights flickered on the ridge that night. And those lights… did not flicker again.

East of the Poison Flats, something sharp and savage awakened. The Scraps Queens, already feared for their feral organisation, saw two new names carved into their lore:

Sable Fang, who speaks only in commands

Aria Dark, who sings to the dead—and they listen

Their arrival was not subtle. Smoke rose. Screams were heard. Whether from training… or testing… none can say. But nearby tribes have started locking their scrap gates.

And then there was elegance. Velvet and venom.

From the ruins of a collapsed shopping centre, Flint’s Floozies emerged wearing fur, chrome, and confidence. Vera Crez and Talis Ember took their places beside AuntyAndy, not with roars—but with a raised eyebrow and a loaded pistol.

They sent out just one scout. One. To watch. The wasteland noticed.

Beneath the shadow of a crumbled satellite dish, gears turned. Smoke coiled into the air in purposeful spirals. The Gear Grinders awoke with the scream of steel.

And with them, Terrara—a chief born not of blood, but of flame and oil. Some say she forged her own heart. Others say she tore it out of an enemy.

Whatever the truth, the Grinders now move with terrifying unity. And where once there were ruins, now there are structures.

Farther west, past the black lakes, silence clings to the hills. There is a tribe gathering strength in the stillness: the Bunny Boilers. Their chief Mitch is said to speak in riddles. Their second, Bunney, just smiles too much.

They haven't moved. Not obviously. But the birds have stopped flying above their camp. And that usually means someone’s building something loud.

And as for the others—Z, Labrador, even whispers of Utopia—no chiefs yet announced. But watchers have spotted movement. Flickers of torchlight. Shapes in the fog.

It is the pause before thunder.

💬 SCRAPS OF GOSSIP
"You can tell who’s serious by how fast they find a chief. You can tell who’s dangerous by how many they find in one day."
– Old techwitch proverb, etched on a microwave door

“Fizzell has a plan. It involves maths. You should be afraid.”
– Mysterious graffiti near Sector 33

“Aria Dark’s song killed a dog.”
– Debunked. Probably. Maybe. We don’t actually know where the dog is.

🔥 THE WASTELAND BREATHES
No battles yet. But the signs are there:

Scrap heaps picked clean overnight

Strange, symmetrical footprints in the salt dunes

A single broken spear stuck upright in a rabbit skull outside The Night Bone’s last known camp

Someone’s sending messages. And someone else… is reading them.

🔮 COMING NEXT ISSUE
Who else will rise?

What happens when the first chiefs meet?

And what, exactly, is being built beneath the sand near 051.040?

The world is watching. The dust is listening.

Are you?

newsletters.title: AND THE GOOD NEWS IS THERE IS NO FUCKIN GOOD NEWS
newsletters.content:
💔 The Mitch Mishap: A Chief Gone Rogue (And Back Again)
This cycle’s juiciest scandal centres on a certain fearsome warrior — Chief Mitch — who found herself waking up in a tribe she didn’t recognise.

She’d been mistakenly registered, temporarily absorbed into a camp that wasn’t hers. One morning she vanished, leaving only empty bowls, half-told jokes, and perhaps a slightly unnerved warlord who insisted, "She enjoyed the sausage and smash."

Now, Mitch is returning home. But tensions are high. The real owner of her warband is sharpening weapons, whispering curses, and threatening vengeance so complete it might be taught in future strategy manuals.

Wasteland politics are tricky. But Mitch? Mitch doesn’t do politics. She does revenge.

📈 TRIBE HIGHLIGHTS
🏴 The Scorched Earth
New blood has joined the tribe as scouts fan out into the fog. Scavengers are hunting for old tech and hidden caches, while the garrison remains locked, loaded, and hungry for opportunity. The scorched are stirring.

🥄 Brian McClair
Well-oiled and ready, this tribe sent out multiple chiefs to scavenge key points. While their troopers didn’t bring back fame or fortune just yet, the groundwork has been laid. A build-up is coming.

🐇 Bunney’s Bunny Boilers
Where there are bunnies, there is mischief. Their scouts are out, and their actions have certainly made an impact — not for wealth or warfare, but for daring to accidentally hold onto someone else's beloved chief. Good luck, Bunney.

⚙️ The Gear Grinders
The forges burn bright. More weapons have been hammered together, and despite a minor hiccup with an outpost attempt, their stockpiles are growing. There’s a storm brewing behind their mechanical minds.

👑 The Scraps Queens
A tribe in motion — recruiting, resting, rearming. Their troops are energised, their camps expanding, and their chiefs walking with just a bit more swagger than last turn. Momentum? Oh yes.

🌸 Utopian Amazons
After scouring distant hexes, the Amazons are hauling home success and pushing their reach further with each step. No chiefs yet, but who needs titles when you’ve got that kind of efficiency?

💩 $hit Hot
They’ve been everywhere — quietly scooping up scrap, food, and likely anything else that wasn’t nailed down. While others shout, they stockpile. This tribe is building something, and it won’t be subtle when it arrives.

🧠 Shiftheads
A staggering number of chiefs have entered their ranks — enough to start a monarchy or maybe even a small religion. Whether this becomes a logistical nightmare or an unstoppable juggernaut is yet to be seen. Either way, Ange El is in — and something tells us she won’t be idle for long.

💋 Ladies of the Night
They’ve swept out of their lair with scouts and scavengers. There’s a growing sense that this tribe’s about to stop whispering and start slashing. Chief Sue-Ki carries herself like someone with unfinished business.

🛠️ Others in Motion
From warriors quietly mustering at garrisons to tribes setting up footholds in forgotten corners, many camps are preparing for something big. The map may be quiet — but it’s the kind of quiet that comes right before the sky cracks open.

🛠️ STATE OF THE WASTES
Chiefs are arriving in droves — legends in the making, or names destined for lost bones.

Camps are building, shifting, and stockpiling.

Alliances are being whispered… and betrayals are being plotted.

And Mitch? Mitch is watching.

🔮 LOOKING AHEAD
As next turns roll out, keep an eye on:

The fallout from the Mitch situation — revenge, redemption, or full-blown tribal warfare?

A potential rise in tribal movement across contested hexes.

New chief dramas — because if you thought Mitch was spicy, wait until two tribes register the same twin sisters…

Remember, in Radix Tribes, you don’t just survive — you earn your legend.

And one wrong move? That’s someone else’s victory song.

🕵️‍♀️ RUMOUR MILL – “Truth is optional.”
Compiled by unnamed scouts and a suspiciously well-dressed crow.

🐍 A tribe in the East is said to be offering scrap for secrets. They claim it’s for “mapping purposes,” but several chiefs have since mysteriously changed hexes.

🎭 Two chiefs with the same name were spotted drinking together — despite allegedly being on opposite sides of the map. Cloning? Trickery? Or just very lazy parents?

🐢 Someone’s building a base. Slowly. Quietly. But survivors say they've seen “gleaming metal rising from the dunes.” No one's admitting it's them. Which makes it worse.

🔥 The owner of Mitch is said to be writing names on bullets. One for every tribe. Only one is carved deeper than the rest.

🕸️ A chief once lost to the wastes may have returned... but not as she once was. The camp that claimed her went silent. All we heard was the sound of skittering.

👑 A new warband is forming in secret. No tribal banners. No official records. But chiefs keep disappearing and reappearing wearing strange red feathers.

newsletters.title: Territory War Incoming
newsletters.content:
Tribes are no longer just “settling” the wastes. They’re branding it, planting their banners into the sand like war stakes. With garrisons going up faster than excuses in a war council, the age of exploration is officially OVER.

If your tribe isn’t building, scouting, or expanding — then someone is doing it to you.

🎤 TRIBAL PROPAGANDA
🧠 Shiftheads:
"We don’t move fast. You move slow. That’s the difference."
Now with so many chiefs deployed it’s hard to tell if they’re playing Radix Tribes or reenacting D-Day. Spoiler: it’s working.

⚙️ Gear Grinders:
"Every time you blink, we build another camp. Keep blinking."
Reinforcements have been flowing like oil. Territories carved, units bolstered. There’s a chill when they pass, and the smell of burning iron.

💋 Ladies of the Night:
"Beauty. Brains. Brutality. We’ve got all three. You’ve got time. For now."
Their hex spread is calculated. The gossip? Worse. Someone whispered they don’t sleep. Someone else disappeared after saying that.

💩 $hit Hot:
"Speak softly and carry a garrison."
They’re not just hot — they’re simmering. Word is they’re setting up for something big. The kind of big that starts with a flash and ends with someone’s tribe name crossed off the ledger.

🏴 Scorched Earth:
"If you see us, it’s already too late."
These maniacs don’t scout. They invade. Some claim their map is just marked “YES” and “SOON.”

🧟‍♂️ RUMOUR MILL – “The desert never lies. People do.”
🐚 A strange radio signal was picked up in Hex 14, repeating an unintelligible word: "Ourobax." No one’s claimed responsibility. But one camp near there? Gone. Like… totally gone.

🧃 A food drop was intercepted and replaced with “unusual meat.” No tribe has confessed to it — but three chiefs have developed glowing eyes since.

🔥 A chief with no known tribe has been spotted riding a rust-beast. She doesn’t speak. She doesn’t stop. She just carves names into rocks and moves on. Two of the names were later confirmed dead.

💾 Someone found a data shard buried under a collapsed ruin. It contains coordinates, numbers… and a voice that says, “You are not the first.”

🐍 A betrayal is whispered in backchannels. One chief has already cut a deal to double-cross their own tribe. They haven’t done it yet — but the knife is ready.

☠️ MOST WANTED TRIBES – Wasteland Watchlist
Shiftheads – Expansion beasts. Either build an alliance or build a grave.

Gear Grinders – Cold, calculated, and everywhere.

Ladies of the Night – Growing faster than a bad fungus on irradiated fruit.

Scrap Queens – Quietly lethal, tactically surgical.

$hit Hot – The wildcard. No one’s sure what they’re doing… which is the scariest thing of all.

Dishonourable Mention: The tribe that tried to register a chief they didn’t own… again. The wasteland doesn’t forget. And neither does Mitch.

🧿 WHISPERS FROM THE VOID
"The centre will open. When it does, they’ll come for what you’ve built."
— An old scavenger’s final words, overheard in a trader camp.

"Don’t die stupid."
— Spray-painted on a burnt garrison wall.

🧨 NEXT TURN TEASE
One hex is glowing. No one’s admitting why.

A Neutral Event is coming… and it has consequences.

One tribe will face an internal dilemma. You’ll know it when it hits.

The “Ourobax Signal” may go public… but at what cost?

newsletters.title: Echoes from the Ashes
newsletters.content:
The wastelands fell silent again as Turn 4 began, but whispers of past deeds drift on the scorched winds, accompanied now by rumors and wild speculation. Tribes across the land stir beneath the apparent calm, each harboring secrets, ambitions, and possibly darker intentions...

Scorched Earth has rallied strongly, forging weapons and recruiting new warriors to their banner. Their granaries overflow—a sign they might be readying for war or simply ensuring survival against unseen foes. Chief Finland's arrival fuels whispers of bold, moonlit battle plans etched into ash-covered maps.

In the east, Brian McClair built anew, establishing strategic outposts and crafting weapons. An influx of fresh chiefs—Synth, Mara Solis, Mina Shae, and Fizzell—speaks volumes. Whispers grow louder about shadowy meetings and midnight alliances shaping their destiny.

Bunney’s Bunny Boilers sent scouts across dusty trails, often returning empty-handed but laden with critical knowledge. Chiefs Mitch and Bunney inspire curiosity, their encampments rumored to host strange rituals and eerie chants echoing beneath the stars.

Flint’s Floozies, tireless explorers, relentlessly mapped the wilds. Their persistent searches hint at strategic ambitions greater than mere survival. Travelers have spoken of distant flares and concealed trails, suggesting Flint’s Floozies know secrets others only dream of.

Utopian Amazons, having recruited vast numbers rapidly, now sit atop abundant resources. Are their warriors destined for conquest or to fortify defenses? Nearby tribes whisper about elaborate war paints, fierce chants, and tribal drums beating ominously through the night.

$hit Hot enjoys an advantage none can fully fathom. Their scavengers' successful raids gathered valuable scrap, and with chiefs Ruby Red, Pixie, and Eve Raze joining their ranks, flamboyant ferocity lies ahead. Whispers of guarded secret technologies stir envy and fear.

Behind fortified walls, the Shiftheads gather strength and leadership, assembling an unprecedented council of chiefs. Such an assembly must have purpose—whispers speculate something extraordinary or explosive approaches, underscored by strange lights and plumes of smoke rising ominously from their encampment.

Sue, Grabbit and Run advance steadily toward mastering scavenging techniques. Their scholars' quiet determination may alter their tribe's fate dramatically. Yet such knowledge brings risk—rumors suggest powerful rivals eye their progress hungrily.

To the north, The Night Bone remain enigmatic, their silence thickening suspicions of impending surprises. Whispers hint they’re gathering strength secretly for a decisive strike.

Gear Grinders, quiet but resilient, keep their secrets well-hidden. Chief Terrara’s arrival hints at possible change, though their plans remain concealed beneath layers of rust and oil.

Scraps Queens enjoy high morale, their quiet confidence hinting at hidden reserves of strength and potential secret alliances whispered about by fireside storytellers.

Z maneuvers silently across multiple strongholds, a quiet redistribution of forces sparking curiosity among their neighbors. Are these simply strategic adjustments, or preludes to expansion?

Maxikazistanisjantown moves troops skillfully, their strategic placements like pieces on a grand chessboard. Chief Amethyst’s arrival adds mystery; rumors suggest they might soon reveal their grand design.

Meanwhile, Jinx, Moriarty, Wonderland, Shaman, and StonedVikings quietly maintain their vigil, their true intentions cloaked in secrecy, though campfire tales circulate of hidden caches and concealed plots waiting patiently beneath calm facades.

And so, warriors, leaders, and dreamers, the wasteland waits once more. Listen closely to its whispers and heed its tales, for within lie hidden clues of battles yet to unfold. Your destiny approaches—choose wisely your next move.

newsletters.title: “Whispers from the Dust, Screams in the Wind”
newsletters.content:
🩸 Tensions Boil, Blades Are Sharpened
The quiet before the storm? Not anymore. Turn 5 brought motion—bold, beautiful, and bloody in intent. Veteran tribes are moving with clear purpose, while new forces enter the map, stirring old grudges and brewing brand-new ones.

🔥 TRIBAL SPOTLIGHTS
💋 Ladies of the Night
Subtle as a knife in the back, and twice as deadly. Their continued silence belies deadly intent. Scouts report erratic flashes in the dark and strange shapes etched into the sand near their hexes. Something's coming.

🧨 Scrap Queens
Steady, silent, and extremely well-fed. Their logistics game is tight. Whispers hint at quiet alliances, buried caches, and garrisons that aren’t as empty as they appear.

💩 $hit Hot
Still steaming from their early dominance, this tribe’s fire hasn’t cooled. A fresh batch of supplies and their uncanny ability to be everywhere at once has their rivals sweating bullets. And we all saw those scrap piles… 👀

🐇 Bunny Boilers
They say madness sleeps in their tents. Scouts have returned, and new garrisons are cropping up. What are they protecting—or hiding? And where is Mitch?

🌸 Utopian Amazons
The Amazons continue to impress, reinforcing their territory and expanding their influence. But power attracts enemies. Have they risen too fast?

🌀 Shiftheads
There’s motion in their camp—movement that feels coordinated. Like pieces being set for a game only they understand. Garrison upgrades? Scouts deployed? Yeah, they’re definitely up to something.

🧠 Sue, Grabbit and Run
Still playing the long game, and maybe winning it. Their scouts are methodical, their hexes secure. Their tech knowledge is increasing… and so is the paranoia from everyone else.

💣 Scorched Earth
Fortified and resourced. Ready for what’s next. The name says it all. If they march, it won’t be for sightseeing.

⚙️ Gear Grinders
Still low on noise, high on mystery. But movement is happening. Chief Terrara is whispering strategy to someone... who’s listening?

👁️ Brian McClair

Subtle as a knife in the back, and twice as deadly. Their continued silence belies deadly intent. Scouts report erratic flashes in the dark and strange shapes etched into the sand near their hexes. Something's coming.

🧨 Scrap Queens
Steady, silent, and extremely well-fed. Their logistics game is tight. Whispers hint at quiet alliances, buried caches, and garrisons that aren’t as empty as they appear.

💩 $hit Hot
Still steaming from their early dominance, this tribe’s fire hasn’t cooled. A fresh batch of supplies and their uncanny ability to be everywhere at once has their rivals sweating bullets. And we all saw those scrap piles… 👀

🐇 Bunny Boilers
They say madness sleeps in their tents. Scouts have returned, and new garrisons are cropping up. What are they protecting—or hiding? And where is Mitch?

🌸 Utopian Amazons
The Amazons continue to impress, reinforcing their territory and expanding their influence. But power attracts enemies. Have they risen too fast?

🌀 Shiftheads
There’s motion in their camp—movement that feels coordinated. Like pieces being set for a game only they understand. Garrison upgrades? Scouts deployed? Yeah, they’re definitely up to something.

Still playing the long game, and maybe winning it. Their scouts are methodical, their hexes secure. Their tech knowledge is increasing… and so is the paranoia from everyone else.

announcements.title: 🖤 In Memory of Dan Hughes
announcements.message:
We are heartbroken to share that Dan Hughes, founder and visionary behind the Radix network, passed away unexpectedly on Sunday night.

Dan’s brilliance and passion built the foundation of everything we do. His legacy lives on in the community he helped create and inspire.

Out of respect, Radix Tribes will pause until 5th August.

Thank you for your understanding as we take this moment to reflect and honour his memory.

— WeAreMonstas
